When this Greenland shark was born, Leonardo painted the Mona Lisa. The species is the longest-lived vertebrate on the planet, living centuries in deep icy waters.    
A first-ever analysis of the whole Greenland shark genome gives researchers a couple of clues to their longevity.&nbsp;

For humans, puberty hits after around a decade. But Greenland sharks have to wait well over 100 years. A century-long childhood might seem like science fiction, but Greenland sharks are the longest-living vertebrate on Earth, with lifespans thought to stretch to around 400 years. These fish spend centuries diving deep into frigid Arctic and Northern Atlantic waters, where they reach massive sizes by growing roughly a centimeter a year. The largest fully grown Greenland sharks can be longer than a Toyotâ€¦

